WEBVTT

00:13.361 --> 00:14.666
Man: Who is teaching us
to be strong?

00:14.797 --> 00:16.059
All: PADRE!

00:16.190 --> 00:17.452
Woman:
He'll train eight-year-olds

00:17.582 --> 00:19.193
to kill
without a good reason.

00:19.323 --> 00:20.890
I know you took out half the
settlement's guards with this.

00:21.021 --> 00:22.631
Back up.
Don't!

00:22.761 --> 00:24.154
What are you doing?!

00:24.285 --> 00:25.460
I brought you here
seven years ago.

00:25.590 --> 00:27.331
I also helped you
and your father escape.

00:27.462 --> 00:28.898
Where are you taking me?

00:29.029 --> 00:31.205
I made a promise to your dad,
and I intend to keep it.

00:31.335 --> 00:32.728
Why was she back at PADRE?

00:32.858 --> 00:34.860
Morgan: They can protect you
in ways that we can't.

00:34.991 --> 00:35.861
How'd they find us?

00:35.992 --> 00:37.907
♪

00:38.038 --> 00:39.430
Woman: Now we have
something to fight for.

00:39.561 --> 00:41.954
♪

01:06.370 --> 01:09.199
[June sighs]

01:12.550 --> 01:20.906
♪

01:21.037 --> 01:29.350
♪

01:29.480 --> 01:31.439
[Walker growling]

01:31.569 --> 01:40.404
♪

01:40.535 --> 01:49.283
♪

01:49.413 --> 01:58.292
♪

01:58.422 --> 02:07.562
♪

02:07.692 --> 02:16.353
♪

02:16.484 --> 02:19.835
Woman:
Warbler, what's your ETA?

02:19.965 --> 02:21.663
Warbler:
10 minutes out.

02:21.793 --> 02:24.013
Hurry up.
Got a lead on an egg.

02:24.144 --> 02:25.536
Might be a whole mess.

02:25.667 --> 02:33.762
♪

02:33.892 --> 02:41.987
♪

02:42.118 --> 02:50.213
♪

02:50.344 --> 02:58.352
♪

02:58.482 --> 03:00.354
[Clicking]

03:00.484 --> 03:07.839
♪

03:07.970 --> 03:09.363
[Grunts][Gun fires]

03:09.493 --> 03:18.981
♪

03:19.111 --> 03:28.599
♪

03:28.730 --> 03:38.478
♪

03:38.609 --> 03:48.053
♪

03:48.184 --> 03:57.759
♪

03:57.889 --> 04:07.682
♪

04:07.812 --> 04:17.300
♪

04:17.430 --> 04:18.779
[Grunts]

04:18.910 --> 04:24.525
♪

04:24.655 --> 04:26.483
[Door creaks]

04:26.614 --> 04:29.878
♪

04:30.008 --> 04:31.009
[Door closes]

04:31.140 --> 04:38.843
♪

04:38.974 --> 04:46.895
♪

04:47.025 --> 04:49.941
Ah, God damn it!
We've been hit. [Man screaming]

04:50.072 --> 04:52.509
I repeat,
we've been hit.

04:52.640 --> 04:54.990
Warbler, is that you?
What happened?

04:55.120 --> 04:56.470
Where are you?

04:56.600 --> 04:58.515
Warbler, come in.

04:58.646 --> 05:00.561
What happened?

05:00.691 --> 05:02.040
What do you think
happened?

05:02.171 --> 05:03.738
That asshole got us.

05:03.868 --> 05:05.696
Cut our goddamn
fingers off.

05:05.827 --> 05:07.219
You should've been ready
for them.

05:07.350 --> 05:09.396
They've been at this shit
for years now.

05:09.526 --> 05:12.268
Oh, spare me your
"I told you so" bullshit.

05:12.399 --> 05:13.791
When I find
this son of a bitch,

05:13.922 --> 05:15.402
I'm gonna cut off
both his hands

05:15.532 --> 05:16.838
and shove them down --[Walkie clicks]

05:16.968 --> 05:25.368
♪

05:25.499 --> 05:33.811
♪

05:36.466 --> 05:39.121
[Birds chirping]

05:57.966 --> 06:01.709
Woman: PADRE 3.
Rescue complete.

06:01.839 --> 06:05.016
Man: Copy, PADRE 3.
En route to you now.

06:16.550 --> 06:18.247
[Knock on door]Man: Hello?

06:18.378 --> 06:19.727
I just wanna talk.

06:22.251 --> 06:25.254
Don't shoot.

06:25.385 --> 06:27.082
Give me one good reason
not to.

06:27.212 --> 06:30.259
Just hear me out.How'd you find this place?

06:30.390 --> 06:31.782
I followed you here.

06:31.913 --> 06:35.438
Please! I'm the one who's been
writing on your signs.

06:35.569 --> 06:37.440
Name's Adrian.
I don't want
to know your name.

06:37.571 --> 06:39.224
I need your help.Can't help you.

06:39.355 --> 06:41.923
My daughter, Hannah --Don't know her.

06:42.053 --> 06:44.360
Collectors took her away from me
years ago, right near here.

06:44.491 --> 06:45.927
I said I don't know her!

06:46.057 --> 06:47.363
Maybe not.

06:47.494 --> 06:49.582
But you know PADRE.

06:49.713 --> 06:52.281
I've seen your signs.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.152
What you've got
in that jar.

06:54.283 --> 06:56.894
I know you can help me.

06:57.025 --> 06:58.156
Get out.

06:58.287 --> 06:59.723
You don't trust me?

06:59.854 --> 07:02.030
I get it.
Ask me whatever you want.

07:02.160 --> 07:04.293
I don't want
to get to know you.
Why not?

07:04.424 --> 07:07.862
Because I don't want
to get to know anybody.

07:07.992 --> 07:10.647
What did they do to you?

07:10.778 --> 07:13.476
Did they take your kid?

07:13.607 --> 07:14.956
Did you take kids
for them?

07:15.086 --> 07:16.305
Get out!

07:16.436 --> 07:19.874
And don't come back.

07:20.004 --> 07:21.136
Hey!
Whoa!

07:21.266 --> 07:22.920
This is my daughter.
This is Hannah.

07:23.051 --> 07:25.401
This is Hannah.

07:25.532 --> 07:28.926
She was 7 when
this picture was taken.

07:29.057 --> 07:30.493
She'd be 12 now.

07:32.843 --> 07:34.105
That bracelet?

07:39.763 --> 07:42.026
She made one
for each of us.

07:47.205 --> 07:49.469
Please.

07:52.428 --> 07:54.256
I said I can't help you.

07:57.868 --> 08:00.175
I-I'm gonna be back here
every day.

08:02.873 --> 08:06.616
There are a lot
of like-minded people out here

08:06.747 --> 08:08.705
who would help you
with what you're doing.

08:08.836 --> 08:11.186
We're forming an army
to take on PADRE.

08:11.316 --> 08:12.753
You could be a part of it.

08:12.883 --> 08:15.756
I see you here again,
I'll kill you.

08:15.886 --> 08:19.586
I think you're just saying that
to scare me off.

08:19.716 --> 08:21.544
What I want to know
is why.

08:21.675 --> 08:23.764
Let me give you
a piece of advice.

08:23.894 --> 08:26.506
If PADRE has had your daughter
this long,

08:26.636 --> 08:29.117
you're not
getting her back.

08:29.247 --> 08:30.553
Why not?

08:30.684 --> 08:31.554
Because they use
the people

08:31.685 --> 08:35.775
you care about the most
against you.

08:35.905 --> 08:37.952
I'm not gonna stop
looking for her.

08:38.082 --> 08:40.345
Not now.

08:40.476 --> 08:42.390
Not after all this time.

08:42.522 --> 08:45.525
So you can either
kill me...

08:45.655 --> 08:48.005
or help me.

08:48.136 --> 08:49.529
But I'm not giving up.

08:55.709 --> 08:58.276
Adrian:
I'm not giving up!

08:58.407 --> 08:59.930
We know who you are now.

09:00.061 --> 09:01.671
We'll be back.

09:09.984 --> 09:18.601
♪

09:18.732 --> 09:27.175
♪

09:27.305 --> 09:35.749
♪

09:35.879 --> 09:44.627
♪

09:44.758 --> 09:53.375
♪

10:01.949 --> 10:03.515
[Gun fires]

10:03.646 --> 10:05.430
[Man shouts indistinctly,
gun fires]

10:05.561 --> 10:06.823
[Click]

10:41.162 --> 10:42.076
[Knife thuds]

10:51.999 --> 10:54.654
♪

10:54.784 --> 10:55.829
Shit.

10:55.959 --> 10:59.484
♪

10:59.615 --> 11:01.095
Shit.

11:01.225 --> 11:02.487
♪

11:02.618 --> 11:04.054
Don't move.[Gun clicks]

11:04.185 --> 11:10.321
♪

11:10.452 --> 11:12.541
I didn't know there were kids
on board.

11:12.672 --> 11:15.718
Where did you --I hid under the tarp
when you shot them.

11:15.849 --> 11:17.807
Can you
put the gun down?

11:17.938 --> 11:19.156
I'm telling PADRE
what you did.

11:19.287 --> 11:20.462
Don't do that.

11:20.592 --> 11:22.203
♪

11:22.333 --> 11:25.728
Please, don't do that.

11:25.859 --> 11:29.427
PADRE two,
our boat got attacked.

11:29.558 --> 11:32.735
PADRE 2: Finch?
Where's Whistler?

11:32.866 --> 11:35.520
Dead.
She killed him.

11:35.651 --> 11:37.827
And Red Kite and Starling?

11:37.958 --> 11:39.524
She knocked them out.[Both groan softly]

11:39.655 --> 11:41.483
What's your location?

11:41.613 --> 11:42.876
Where are we?

11:43.006 --> 11:45.356
♪

11:45.487 --> 11:46.793
[Gunshot]

11:46.923 --> 11:48.359
Hey. Hey.
Whoa.

11:48.490 --> 11:50.753
June: Damn it.

11:50.884 --> 11:53.321
Repeat, Finch,
where are you?

11:53.451 --> 11:55.758
June, is that you?

11:55.889 --> 11:58.195
[Groaning]
Shit.

12:03.287 --> 12:04.854
She shot you
with her darts.

12:04.985 --> 12:06.116
She was trying
to steal the boat.

12:06.247 --> 12:07.639
Holy shit.

12:07.770 --> 12:09.554
It's you cutting
people's fingers off.

12:09.685 --> 12:11.121
-No, no.
-Dwight, let go!

12:11.252 --> 12:12.644
No, I don't think so.

12:12.775 --> 12:14.211
Why is she
calling you Dwight?

12:16.997 --> 12:19.390
You ran way from PADRE to --
to -- to do this?

12:19.521 --> 12:21.175
It doesn't matter.

12:21.305 --> 12:22.567
You used to be at PADRE?

12:22.698 --> 12:24.482
We don't have time
for another boat.

12:24.613 --> 12:25.962
What are you saying?

12:26.093 --> 12:27.834
Look, you don't have to
answer our questions.

12:27.964 --> 12:29.792
But he needs help.

12:29.923 --> 12:32.012
Alright, we think
he has appendicitis.

12:32.142 --> 12:33.796
He -- He needs surgery.Take him to the clinic.

12:33.927 --> 12:35.667
What do you think
we were doing?

12:35.798 --> 12:37.800
We've got a patrol heading out.
Do you copy, Finch?

12:37.931 --> 12:39.976
Tell them where we are,
Red Kite.

12:41.412 --> 12:43.371
-Hey.
-No.

12:43.501 --> 12:44.981
Why not?

12:45.112 --> 12:46.504
She's gonna
do the surgery.

12:46.635 --> 12:47.897
Dwight, no.
She's a nurse.

12:48.028 --> 12:48.942
You were taking him
to the clinic.

12:49.072 --> 12:50.290
Someone there will be able
to help you.

12:50.421 --> 12:51.858
Sherry:
That's 20 miles from here.

12:51.988 --> 12:53.685
His appendix could burst
by the time

12:53.816 --> 12:55.296
we get back there
on foot.

12:55.426 --> 12:57.254
I don't have what I need
in my kit to do an appendectomy.

12:57.385 --> 12:58.821
Well, you need
to figure it out.

12:58.952 --> 13:00.823
And why is that?

13:00.954 --> 13:03.173
'Cause if you don't,
I'm gonna tell PADRE

13:03.304 --> 13:06.220
who's been cutting off
all his Collectors' fingers.

13:08.744 --> 13:10.354
I just wanted to leave.

13:10.485 --> 13:11.616
Why?

13:11.747 --> 13:14.837
Because...

13:14.968 --> 13:16.752
it's not safe
for me here anymore.

13:16.883 --> 13:18.710
[Groaning]

13:18.841 --> 13:21.365
Hey, buddy.
You alright?

13:21.496 --> 13:25.152
Why don't you hop off the boat
for a minute, okay?

13:25.282 --> 13:28.503
Alright.Hey, remember
what I taught you.

13:28.633 --> 13:30.548
You see Carrion --

13:30.679 --> 13:31.419
Aim for the eyes.

13:31.549 --> 13:32.855
Yeah.
I got it.

13:32.986 --> 13:33.856
Alright.

13:36.990 --> 13:38.730
Why are you
making me do this?

13:38.861 --> 13:40.689
Why are you making us
make you do this, June?

13:40.820 --> 13:43.648
What the hell
happened to you?

13:43.779 --> 13:45.302
Look, I'll tell you what.

13:45.433 --> 13:47.914
You do the surgery, we'll --
we'll get you a boat.

13:48.044 --> 13:50.438
You -- You could take it
wherever the hell you want,

13:50.568 --> 13:52.396
and PADRE will never know
it was you.

13:58.794 --> 14:00.448
That's your kid,
isn't it?

14:00.578 --> 14:03.146
The one you were pregnant with
when they found us on the rafts.

14:03.277 --> 14:04.321
[Sighs]

14:08.804 --> 14:10.762
Does PADRE know?

14:10.893 --> 14:14.070
He -- He doesn't know that,
uh -- that Dwight's the father.

14:14.201 --> 14:15.985
He said he's
been teaching him.

14:16.116 --> 14:18.553
He teaches all the kids.
Combat training.

14:18.683 --> 14:20.468
They, uh --
They call him Red Kite.

14:20.598 --> 14:21.904
And you?

14:22.035 --> 14:24.341
PADRE's got me
in the nursery.

14:24.472 --> 14:28.868
And -- And Finch doesn't know
about either of us.

14:28.998 --> 14:30.608
How'd you get
on the boat?

14:30.739 --> 14:32.349
PADRE would never let you
spend time with your own kid.

14:32.480 --> 14:34.395
I got myself
reassigned.

14:34.525 --> 14:35.570
So you lied?

14:35.700 --> 14:39.052
We've been following
PADRE's rules.

14:39.182 --> 14:41.054
We haven't spent time
together in years.

14:41.184 --> 14:44.274
We wanted to make sure
Finch was okay.

14:44.405 --> 14:45.754
And then?

14:45.885 --> 14:48.800
Once the surgery's done,
we'll take him back,

14:48.931 --> 14:53.980
and no one
will be the wiser, right?

14:54.110 --> 14:55.851
Everything will go back
to how it was.

14:55.982 --> 14:57.505
[Groaning]

14:57.635 --> 15:01.726
♪

15:01.857 --> 15:03.293
Please.

15:03.424 --> 15:06.427
♪

15:06.557 --> 15:08.951
I know where we can
do the surgery.
Where?

15:09.082 --> 15:10.648
I don't want to answer
any questions.

15:10.779 --> 15:12.389
I will take you there.
We will do this.

15:12.520 --> 15:13.782
But then you need to hold up
your end of the deal

15:13.913 --> 15:14.522
and get me that boat.

15:14.652 --> 15:16.524
We will.

15:16.654 --> 15:18.874
Come on.
Let's go.

15:19.005 --> 15:21.921
♪

15:25.750 --> 15:30.712
♪

15:30.842 --> 15:35.891
♪

15:36.022 --> 15:38.198
[Door creaks]

15:38.328 --> 15:39.982
♪

15:40.113 --> 15:41.549
[Flashlight bangs]

15:41.679 --> 15:42.767
[Switch clicks]

15:42.898 --> 15:51.124
♪

15:51.254 --> 15:59.393
♪

15:59.523 --> 16:01.525
[Walker growling]

16:01.656 --> 16:07.836
♪

16:07.967 --> 16:10.317
Dwight: This is where you want
to do the surgery?

16:10.447 --> 16:12.058
Yeah, how'd you even know
about this place?

16:12.188 --> 16:14.712
[Growling continues]

16:14.843 --> 16:16.801
Uh, why is that there?

16:16.932 --> 16:18.586
[Growling]

16:18.716 --> 16:20.283
Jesus.

16:20.414 --> 16:21.719
You sure this place is safe,
June?

16:21.850 --> 16:23.591
♪

16:23.721 --> 16:24.374
[Growling stops]

16:24.505 --> 16:27.812
♪

16:27.943 --> 16:29.162
It is now.

16:29.292 --> 16:34.732
♪

16:34.863 --> 16:36.256
[Whirring]

16:36.386 --> 16:38.171
[Beep]

16:38.301 --> 16:44.829
♪

16:44.960 --> 16:51.575
♪

16:51.706 --> 16:58.278
♪

16:58.408 --> 17:00.628
June: Take this.
It'll help you fall asleep.

17:00.758 --> 17:08.505
♪

17:08.636 --> 17:10.637
[Grunts]

17:10.768 --> 17:13.858
♪

17:13.989 --> 17:16.339
Hey, I'm ready to start
the anesthesia.

17:16.470 --> 17:19.167
♪

17:19.299 --> 17:21.083
[Monitor beeping]Will it hurt?

17:21.214 --> 17:24.304
No, sweetie, no.
You won't feel a thing.

17:24.434 --> 17:28.482
And when you wake up,
you'll feel all better.

17:28.612 --> 17:29.526
Oh.

17:29.657 --> 17:32.877
Uh, and I...

17:33.008 --> 17:35.489
brought that.
[Chuckles]

17:35.619 --> 17:37.317
Why would you bring that?I don't know.

17:37.447 --> 17:38.883
It's -- You know,
there's nothing like waking up

17:39.014 --> 17:40.146
to a new-car smell.

17:40.276 --> 17:42.583
[Laughs]

17:42.713 --> 17:45.368
Uh, Sherry, can you get me
the airway from that shelf?

17:45.499 --> 17:46.369
Mm.

17:46.500 --> 17:54.986
♪

17:55.117 --> 17:58.207
Finch: How did they make
a hospital on the train?

17:58.338 --> 17:59.730
Don't worry.
We have everything we need.

17:59.861 --> 18:01.471
Just try and relax.

18:01.602 --> 18:04.039
♪

18:04.170 --> 18:06.781
I'm feeling sleepy.

18:06.911 --> 18:09.479
That's good. That means
the medicine is working.

18:09.610 --> 18:11.133
♪

18:11.264 --> 18:12.830
Sherry,
we need to get started.

18:12.961 --> 18:14.484
Can I talk to you?

18:14.615 --> 18:15.920
Both of you?

18:16.051 --> 18:20.360
♪

18:20.490 --> 18:21.491
[Instrument clinks]

18:21.622 --> 18:24.625
♪

18:24.755 --> 18:26.453
What the hell is this?

18:26.583 --> 18:27.889
Huh?

18:28.019 --> 18:29.369
Who are these people?

18:29.499 --> 18:31.501
No questions.
That was the agreement.

18:31.632 --> 18:33.808
No, no, no.
No, the deal's changed.

18:33.938 --> 18:37.028
You're not laying a hand on him
until you answer some questions.

18:37.159 --> 18:39.944
You asked me
to do this.

18:40.075 --> 18:41.642
Uh, Sherry's right,
June.

18:41.772 --> 18:44.035
You -- You gotta give us
something here.

18:44.166 --> 18:45.646
This is --[Gun cocks]

18:45.776 --> 18:48.736
Hands up.

18:48.866 --> 18:50.564
-Oh, shit.
-Okay.

18:50.694 --> 18:53.306
Who's this?What are you doing
with that kid?

18:53.436 --> 18:55.569
I'm trying to help him.Two Collectors from PADRE?

18:55.699 --> 18:57.179
It's not
what it looks like.

18:57.310 --> 19:00.313
My daughter, Hannah.
PADRE's got her.

19:00.443 --> 19:01.966
One of you knows where she is,
and you're gonna tell me.

19:02.097 --> 19:03.403
Maybe we could
help you.

19:03.533 --> 19:05.013
-Sherry.
-No, she's right.

19:05.144 --> 19:08.016
Look, this does not have to end
in a fight, okay?

19:08.147 --> 19:10.323
I'm sure -- I'm sure
your daughter's fine.

19:10.453 --> 19:12.368
PADRE hasn't
lost a kid yet.

19:12.499 --> 19:14.196
And I teach them how
to protect themselves,

19:14.327 --> 19:15.763
so if you tell me
what she looks like,

19:15.893 --> 19:17.156
then we can figure
something out here.

19:17.286 --> 19:18.766
Man:
Adrian, your location.

19:18.896 --> 19:20.202
Please respond.

19:20.333 --> 19:22.770
♪

19:22.900 --> 19:24.989
[Walkers growling]

19:25.120 --> 19:29.994
♪

19:30.125 --> 19:31.387
Oh.

19:33.302 --> 19:34.738
Adrian, where are you?

19:34.869 --> 19:36.349
No, no, no.

19:36.479 --> 19:38.089
Don't even
think about it.

19:38.220 --> 19:40.222
There are lots of us.
We'll do whatever it takes

19:40.353 --> 19:41.658
to make sure you can't
hurt any more kids.

19:41.789 --> 19:44.270
We brought him here
to save his life, you asshole.

19:44.400 --> 19:45.445
June: We have a problem.

19:45.575 --> 19:47.229
The bullet hit
the control panel.

19:47.360 --> 19:48.752
I can't do the surgery
without power.

19:48.883 --> 19:50.885
[Finch groaning]

19:51.015 --> 19:52.365
Please, it hurts!

19:52.495 --> 19:54.062
[Groaning]

19:54.193 --> 19:56.456
Dwight.

19:56.586 --> 19:58.893
There's an emergency override
at the back of the train.

19:59.023 --> 20:02.113
If we can turn it on,
we'll have the power we need.

20:04.507 --> 20:06.248
You're lucky.

20:06.379 --> 20:08.685
I'll go.

20:08.816 --> 20:09.860
Come watch him.

20:09.991 --> 20:12.298
[Groaning continues]

20:18.042 --> 20:19.914
June,
get out of my way.

20:20.044 --> 20:21.698
You can't walk
through the train.

20:21.829 --> 20:23.178
Why not?

20:23.309 --> 20:25.311
It's full of the Dead.What?

20:25.441 --> 20:28.749
What are you --
What are you talking about?

20:28.879 --> 20:30.707
Damn it, June, just tell us
what happened here.

20:30.838 --> 20:32.535
I used to work here.

20:32.666 --> 20:34.885
How come we never
heard about it?

20:35.016 --> 20:36.060
It was off the books.

20:36.191 --> 20:38.715
PADRE didn't
want anyone to know.

20:38.846 --> 20:40.978
Experiments
they were conducting.

20:41.109 --> 20:42.763
The walkers,
like the ones in the file?

20:42.893 --> 20:44.504
That woman in the photos,
her name is Shrike.

20:44.634 --> 20:46.288
She works for PADRE.

20:46.419 --> 20:48.290
He wanted her to find a way to
stop the effect of walker bites.

20:48.421 --> 20:49.857
That's not possible.

20:49.987 --> 20:51.946
She thought it was.

20:52.076 --> 20:54.078
She had an idea.
A treatment.

20:54.209 --> 20:55.993
What kind
of treatment?

20:56.124 --> 20:57.865
Radiation.

20:57.995 --> 21:00.911
Slow and painful.

21:01.042 --> 21:02.739
It was worse than dying
from the bites.

21:02.870 --> 21:05.307
Shrike tried to force me
to administer the treatments.

21:05.438 --> 21:07.744
But I wouldn't do it,
so I ran.

21:07.875 --> 21:11.574
[Finch groaning]

21:11.705 --> 21:14.360
We have to get to the back
of the train.

21:14.490 --> 21:16.362
And we can't exactly
go around.

21:16.492 --> 21:18.538
[Walkers growling]

21:18.668 --> 21:20.801
♪

21:20.931 --> 21:22.455
I don't think
we have to.

21:22.585 --> 21:27.024
♪

21:27.155 --> 21:28.896
[Growling continues]

21:29.026 --> 21:34.293
♪

21:38.122 --> 21:40.342
[Walkers growling]

21:45.826 --> 21:48.437
I'm sorry
about all this.

21:48.568 --> 21:50.439
I told you
to stay away from me.

21:50.570 --> 21:52.789
If I had, I wouldn't
have seen this place.

21:52.920 --> 21:54.487
And this shows me you know
even more about PADRE

21:54.617 --> 21:56.967
than you let on before.

21:57.098 --> 21:58.142
I can't help you.

21:58.273 --> 22:00.667
Can't or won't?

22:00.797 --> 22:02.712
Your little sniper attacks,
you're not stopping them.

22:02.843 --> 22:04.845
You're barely
slowing them down.

22:04.975 --> 22:07.021
You want
to do something?

22:07.151 --> 22:09.153
Help me find Hannah.

22:09.284 --> 22:10.807
Or help him.

22:10.938 --> 22:12.809
Get him out of here before
those Collectors come back,

22:12.940 --> 22:14.158
before they take him
back to PADRE.

22:14.289 --> 22:15.769
No.

22:15.899 --> 22:17.423
I can't.

22:17.553 --> 22:19.816
'Cause you're afraid.

22:19.947 --> 22:23.994
You said PADRE used the people
you cared about against you.

22:24.125 --> 22:26.997
You can't run away
from that.

22:27.128 --> 22:29.696
I'm sorry for whatever
happened to you.

22:29.826 --> 22:32.394
Truly.

22:32.525 --> 22:35.484
But if that stops you from
getting close to anyone again,

22:35.615 --> 22:37.791
what exactly
are you living for?

22:37.921 --> 22:40.054
[Electricity whirring]

22:40.184 --> 22:41.621
Dwight:
We back in business?

22:41.751 --> 22:43.318
We are.

22:43.449 --> 22:44.624
How's Finch doing?

22:44.754 --> 22:46.016
He's still asleep,

22:46.147 --> 22:48.758
but the medication
won't last much longer.

22:48.889 --> 22:50.891
Alright, we're on our way
back now.

22:51.021 --> 22:53.372
We'll take that asshole off
your hands when we get there.

22:53.502 --> 22:56.679
♪

22:56.810 --> 22:59.073
[Walkers growling]

23:07.124 --> 23:09.692
[Grunts]

23:09.823 --> 23:12.173
Be careful.
This train's seen better days.

23:14.131 --> 23:15.524
You okay, honey?

23:18.440 --> 23:20.050
What? What?
What is it?

23:20.181 --> 23:24.315
It's just you calling me
"Honey" and seeing Finch.

23:26.274 --> 23:29.146
I can't snap back
to how things used to be.

23:29.277 --> 23:32.541
[Scoffs] I mean, look,
hey, hey, we only have today.

23:32.672 --> 23:34.674
We make the most of that,
you know?

23:34.804 --> 23:37.807
What if we didn't
just have today?

23:37.938 --> 23:40.157
What are you talking about?We made a choice, D, right?

23:40.288 --> 23:42.769
Years ago, when we got
brought in on those rafts,

23:42.899 --> 23:46.120
we said we wouldn't fight back,
we would play by PADRE's rules

23:46.250 --> 23:49.950
because we thought it was
a safe place for our son.

23:50.080 --> 23:51.821
But this?

23:51.952 --> 23:53.127
After what
we saw here today,

23:53.257 --> 23:56.260
I-I can't bring Finch
back here, D.

23:56.391 --> 23:58.262
This doesn't' feel safe.

23:58.393 --> 23:59.916
This feels like --
Sanctuary.

24:00.047 --> 24:01.918
Yeah.

24:02.049 --> 24:03.354
So let's do something
about it.

24:03.485 --> 24:06.793
Like what?
Like leave.

24:06.923 --> 24:09.665
Look, June knows all of
PADRE's collecting grounds.

24:09.796 --> 24:12.494
Right? All of the places
that he would look.

24:12.625 --> 24:13.713
Yeah.

24:13.843 --> 24:17.847
Uh -- Uh -- Uh,
where are we gonna go?

24:17.978 --> 24:20.763
We'll find a place.

24:20.894 --> 24:22.939
And then once we're settled,
we'll find a way

24:23.070 --> 24:26.813
to let everyone inside know
the truth about PADRE.

24:29.206 --> 24:30.686
[Sighs]

24:32.209 --> 24:35.082
You, uh...

24:35.212 --> 24:37.476
You really think we can do this?
Be a family?

24:37.606 --> 24:39.478
This is --
Yes, yes.

24:39.608 --> 24:41.218
I know we can.

24:41.349 --> 24:43.351
Hey, I saw it earlier,

24:43.482 --> 24:47.486
when you gave Finch
that stupid air freshener thing.

24:47.616 --> 24:48.530
♪

24:48.661 --> 24:49.749
Yeah.

24:49.879 --> 24:51.315
We can do this.

24:51.446 --> 24:57.234
♪

24:57.365 --> 24:58.888
Hey.
Oh.

24:59.019 --> 25:03.893
♪

25:04.024 --> 25:06.069
[Creaking]

25:06.200 --> 25:07.506
Shit.

25:07.636 --> 25:09.508
[Electricity crackles]

25:12.554 --> 25:14.382
What the hell's
going on?

25:14.513 --> 25:16.253
Dwight, Sherry,
what happened?

25:16.384 --> 25:18.386
[Walkers growling]

25:18.517 --> 25:20.257
June:
Dwight, Sherry, are you okay?

25:20.388 --> 25:21.955
Shit. Oh! D!

25:22.085 --> 25:23.957
[Gunshot]

25:24.087 --> 25:27.047
♪

25:27.177 --> 25:28.135
[Gunshots]

25:28.265 --> 25:29.571
Ah!

25:29.702 --> 25:30.920
[Gunshot]

25:31.051 --> 25:36.273
♪

25:36.404 --> 25:38.449
[Gunshots]

25:38.580 --> 25:40.234
Dwight: Roof caved in.

25:40.364 --> 25:43.150
We landed in a-a car full of
walkers like I've never seen.

25:43.280 --> 25:45.456
Stay where you are.
I'm on my way.

25:45.587 --> 25:47.676
No, no, no, no.
No, no. It's too risky.

25:47.807 --> 25:50.723
I-I went through all my ammo,
and it wasn't hardly enough.

25:50.853 --> 25:52.507
I'll figure it out. No. No, look.

25:52.638 --> 25:56.163
June, Finch needs you
for the operation, okay?

25:56.293 --> 25:59.601
And, uh, look.

25:59.732 --> 26:01.472
Um...

26:01.603 --> 26:02.822
if we don't make it back,

26:02.952 --> 26:05.172
promise me you will
take care of Finch.

26:05.302 --> 26:06.739
Please promise me.

26:06.869 --> 26:10.960
♪

26:11.091 --> 26:14.485
June.

26:14.616 --> 26:15.878
Stay where you are.
I'm coming.

26:16.009 --> 26:17.880
No, no, June!
Do not c--

26:18.011 --> 26:20.448
Hey. Hey, what the hell
are you doing?

26:20.579 --> 26:22.972
They need to survive.
For him.

26:23.103 --> 26:25.148
Are you doing this because
it's what's best for that kid?

26:25.279 --> 26:26.585
Because you're afraid
you might end up being the one

26:26.715 --> 26:27.934
who has to
take care of him?

26:28.064 --> 26:30.414
♪

26:30.545 --> 26:32.765
Don't follow me.

26:32.895 --> 26:35.289
[Door opens, closes]

26:39.423 --> 26:41.208
[Walkers growling]

26:41.338 --> 26:43.732
[Clanking]

27:17.026 --> 27:18.680
I'm so sorry.

27:18.811 --> 27:20.856
[Growling, clanking continue]

27:28.037 --> 27:34.043
♪

27:34.174 --> 27:40.397
♪

27:40.528 --> 27:42.835
[Rattling]

27:42.965 --> 27:47.709
♪

27:47.840 --> 27:49.102
[Grunts]

27:49.232 --> 27:55.369
♪

27:55.499 --> 27:56.936
Come on!
[Grunts]

27:57.066 --> 28:02.898
♪

28:03.029 --> 28:08.730
♪

28:08.861 --> 28:10.732
[Grunting]

28:10.863 --> 28:16.303
♪

28:16.433 --> 28:22.222
♪

28:22.352 --> 28:24.485
[Gunshots]

28:24.615 --> 28:30.273
♪

28:30.404 --> 28:36.323
♪

28:36.453 --> 28:38.412
[Grunting]

28:40.457 --> 28:42.285
[Breathing heavily]

28:43.939 --> 28:45.811
I told you
not to follow me.

28:45.941 --> 28:47.595
Good thing
I didn't listen.

28:49.684 --> 28:52.208
You should have.

28:52.339 --> 28:55.211
We're a lot alike,
you know that?

28:55.342 --> 29:00.608
The only difference is, I still
have someone to live for.

29:00.739 --> 29:02.566
You need to find yours.

29:02.697 --> 29:07.006
I told you there are
more people like us.

29:07.136 --> 29:10.487
Together, we can
take down PADRE.

29:10.618 --> 29:11.662
I can't help you.

29:11.793 --> 29:12.794
I'm not doing this
for me.

29:12.925 --> 29:14.796
I'm doing it
for Hannah!

29:14.927 --> 29:17.407
♪

29:17.538 --> 29:19.235
[Muffled growling]

29:19.366 --> 29:21.890
I'm going to find her,
whether you help me or not,

29:22.021 --> 29:24.632
and when I do,
I want her to see

29:24.763 --> 29:27.504
her father isn't the man
PADRE says he is.

29:27.635 --> 29:30.377
♪

29:30.507 --> 29:33.467
We should keep moving.

29:33.597 --> 29:34.773
Finch:
I'm coming with you.

29:34.903 --> 29:36.992
♪

29:37.123 --> 29:39.255
It's too dangerous.
You need to go back.

29:39.386 --> 29:41.083
I can handle the Carrion.

29:41.214 --> 29:42.737
Red Kite taught me how.

29:42.868 --> 29:47.873
♪

29:48.003 --> 29:50.179
[Growling]

29:50.310 --> 29:55.097
♪

29:55.228 --> 29:57.621
[Gunshots]

29:57.752 --> 29:59.798
[Finch grunts]

29:59.928 --> 30:01.800
[Body thuds]

30:01.930 --> 30:02.844
How was that?

30:02.975 --> 30:04.846
That was good, kid.

30:04.977 --> 30:06.935
[Walkers growling]

30:13.724 --> 30:15.074
What are you
doing here?

30:15.204 --> 30:19.165
I'm gonna tell PADRE
how I fought the Carrion.

30:19.295 --> 30:23.082
Finch, we're n-- we're not
gonna go back to PADRE.

30:23.212 --> 30:24.953
Why not?Look, we want what's best

30:25.084 --> 30:27.695
for you, and it --
and it's not there.

30:27.826 --> 30:29.610
What are you
talking about?

30:34.310 --> 30:38.880
♪

30:39.011 --> 30:40.664
We're -- We're
your parents.

30:40.795 --> 30:41.927
No, you're not.

30:42.057 --> 30:43.145
Hey.
No.

30:43.276 --> 30:44.668
No.

30:44.799 --> 30:46.714
Okay, I -- sweetie,
I know this is a lot

30:46.845 --> 30:49.325
for you to take in
right now,

30:49.456 --> 30:53.808
but I promise you,
we're gonna figure it out, okay?

30:53.939 --> 30:55.244
As a family.

30:55.375 --> 30:56.463
Yeah.

30:56.593 --> 30:59.814
[Groaning]

30:59.945 --> 31:03.035
Oh. Hey.We really should get him back
to the operating room.

31:03.165 --> 31:05.733
[Groaning]

31:05.864 --> 31:06.865
Let's go.

31:06.995 --> 31:11.608
♪

31:11.739 --> 31:12.479
No.

31:12.609 --> 31:14.873
[Walker growling]

31:15.003 --> 31:18.137
♪

31:18.267 --> 31:19.051
Hannah.

31:19.181 --> 31:26.710
♪

31:26.841 --> 31:28.408
You knew!Hey! Let her go!

31:28.538 --> 31:29.757
That's why you wouldn't help me!
You knew!

31:29.888 --> 31:30.889
-Let her go!
-Get off me!

31:31.019 --> 31:32.586
It's okay.
It's okay.

31:32.716 --> 31:34.631
You killed her.
No.

31:34.762 --> 31:36.155
You did.I tried to save her.

31:36.285 --> 31:37.721
You killed her.

31:37.852 --> 31:40.768
I treated her for asthma
when she first came to PADRE.

31:40.899 --> 31:43.379
She was just
a scared kid.

31:43.510 --> 31:46.382
She missed her dad.

31:46.513 --> 31:48.254
She reminded me
of my daughter.

31:48.384 --> 31:51.387
And I wanted to take care of her
and make her feel safe.

31:51.518 --> 31:53.215
You're a liar.I thought she was.

31:53.346 --> 31:54.390
No, you're a liar.

31:54.521 --> 31:55.957
No, and then she went
on a scout.

31:56.088 --> 31:57.828
She went off-island
and she got bit,

31:57.959 --> 32:00.179
but it was on her back,
and I couldn't amputate,

32:00.309 --> 32:02.224
but I had to
do something.

32:02.355 --> 32:04.183
I had to save her.

32:04.313 --> 32:08.274
That woman -- Shrike --

32:08.404 --> 32:10.711
she put my Hannah
through that treatment?

32:10.841 --> 32:14.149
♪

32:14.280 --> 32:16.108
It wasn't her treatment.
It was mine.

32:16.238 --> 32:18.240
♪

32:18.371 --> 32:19.807
What are you
talking about?

32:19.938 --> 32:21.200
I saw someone
survive a bite

32:21.330 --> 32:23.202
longer than anyone
I had ever seen,

32:23.332 --> 32:24.986
and she'd been exposed
to radiation,

32:25.117 --> 32:27.641
so I thought
if it worked for her,

32:27.771 --> 32:28.685
it could work for Hannah.

32:28.816 --> 32:30.035
Youdid this to her?

32:30.165 --> 32:32.124
I gave her radiotherapy

32:32.254 --> 32:36.171
with equipment that we scavenged
from a hospital.

32:36.302 --> 32:38.608
It stopped the infection.

32:38.739 --> 32:42.873
But the amount of radiation
that it took...

32:43.004 --> 32:45.006
just made things
worse for her,

32:45.137 --> 32:46.703
and I wanted to end
her suffering.

32:46.834 --> 32:47.878
So why didn't you?!

32:48.009 --> 32:48.923
Because Shrike
wouldn't let me!

32:49.054 --> 32:51.230
She wanted
to let her turn!

32:51.360 --> 32:52.535
♪

32:52.666 --> 32:53.754
Why?

32:53.884 --> 32:56.278
♪

32:56.409 --> 32:58.193
Why?!

32:58.324 --> 33:01.153
So she could study her.

33:01.283 --> 33:03.807
See how long it took.

33:03.938 --> 33:05.374
And you let her?

33:05.505 --> 33:07.028
I didn't have a choice!

33:07.159 --> 33:08.464
She held a gun on me

33:08.595 --> 33:10.901
and she said as long as
her finger was on the trigger,

33:11.032 --> 33:13.034
I had to keep
the experiments going,

33:13.165 --> 33:16.168
or other people
would pay the price.

33:16.298 --> 33:17.647
That's how this
whole place happened,

33:17.778 --> 33:20.389
because I tried to save
someone I cared about.

33:20.520 --> 33:23.958
And PADRE made sure that other
people suffered as a result.

33:24.089 --> 33:26.439
So I made sure Shrike
couldn't do to anyone else

33:26.569 --> 33:30.617
what she did to me,
and I took her trigger finger.

33:30.747 --> 33:34.403
I knew they couldn't do
the experiments without me,

33:34.534 --> 33:37.450
which meant as long
as I stayed away from here...

33:37.580 --> 33:39.495
♪

33:39.626 --> 33:42.716
...stayed away
from people,

33:42.846 --> 33:45.414
no one else I cared about
could get hurt.

33:45.545 --> 33:52.421
♪

33:52.552 --> 33:59.559
♪

33:59.689 --> 34:06.740
♪

34:06.870 --> 34:08.437
She was all I had left.

34:08.568 --> 34:17.185
♪

34:17.315 --> 34:21.885
I understand now
why you want to be alone.

34:22.016 --> 34:29.676
♪

34:29.806 --> 34:37.466
♪

34:37.597 --> 34:39.251
[Growling]

34:39.380 --> 34:46.822
♪

34:46.954 --> 34:54.353
♪

34:54.483 --> 34:55.876
Adrian!

34:56.005 --> 34:57.356
Adrian, no!

34:57.486 --> 35:01.099
♪

35:01.229 --> 35:03.579
I gotcha. Oh.

35:03.710 --> 35:05.712
I'm sorry, baby.

35:05.842 --> 35:08.845
Please forgive me.

35:08.976 --> 35:11.805
[Walkers growling]

35:11.935 --> 35:13.633
[Adrian screaming]

35:13.763 --> 35:20.118
♪

35:23.425 --> 35:26.036
[Monitor beeping]

35:26.167 --> 35:28.691
[Walkers growling in distance]

35:32.652 --> 35:34.219
[Instrument clinks]

35:40.181 --> 35:42.749
He's stable.
He should be awake soon.

35:42.879 --> 35:45.621
Thank you.

35:45.752 --> 35:47.841
I held up
my end of the deal.

35:47.971 --> 35:49.495
You should arrange
for that boat.

35:51.975 --> 35:54.935
We will,
uh, but, June...

35:55.065 --> 35:59.635
look, when it gets here, we want
us all to get on it together.

36:00.941 --> 36:02.551
No.
We agreed.

36:02.682 --> 36:04.031
Well, things
have changed, June.

36:04.162 --> 36:05.250
For who?

36:06.599 --> 36:10.646
When Finch wakes up, we're gonna
take him away from this place.

36:10.777 --> 36:16.043
Yeah. We're -- We're gonna try
and be a family.

36:16.174 --> 36:18.001
What's that
got to do with me?

36:18.132 --> 36:21.091
You're family.

36:21.222 --> 36:23.398
We know what happened
to you, June.

36:23.529 --> 36:24.878
We understand
why you left

36:25.008 --> 36:28.273
and why you've been
out here on your own,

36:28.403 --> 36:31.624
but we can't let you
end up like Adrian.

36:31.754 --> 36:33.147
What's that
supposed to mean?

36:33.278 --> 36:37.107
As someone who doesn't
have anybody to live for.

36:38.500 --> 36:40.154
Look,
I've told you before,

36:40.285 --> 36:45.203
but I wouldn't be here
if it weren't for you and John.

36:47.422 --> 36:53.515
You know, I have a, uh --
a family because of that,

36:53.646 --> 36:57.215
and I want you
to be a part of it.

36:57.345 --> 36:59.042
That's, uh,
if you want to.

36:59.173 --> 37:06.224
♪

37:06.354 --> 37:07.486
Okay.

37:07.616 --> 37:12.317
♪

37:12.447 --> 37:15.755
Adrian saved me so I could
find someone to live for.

37:15.885 --> 37:16.843
[Chuckles]

37:16.973 --> 37:20.412
♪

37:20.542 --> 37:23.328
[Sighs]
I just need to do something.

37:23.458 --> 37:25.330
I need to go
put Hannah to rest.

37:25.460 --> 37:28.724
And Adrian, too.
They've suffered enough.

37:28.855 --> 37:29.986
Yeah.
We're right here.

37:30.117 --> 37:35.992
♪

