Wake up, Finch!
Finch, wake up!

40:18.807 --> 40:19.678
Stop it!

40:19.808 --> 40:21.331
Finch, wake up!Wake up, Finch!

40:21.462 --> 40:23.290
Finch, wake up!Stop! Please stop!

40:23.421 --> 40:24.944
-Stop it!
-Finch!

40:25.074 --> 40:26.249
Wake up!

40:26.380 --> 40:27.599
No, no.
Finch!

40:27.729 --> 40:29.470
No, please! Please!Please wake up, Finch!

40:29.601 --> 40:31.951
Finch!
Finch!

40:32.081 --> 40:33.648
Stop it!
Stop!

40:33.779 --> 40:35.215
No! Wake up, Finch!
Wake up!

40:35.345 --> 40:36.869
Finch!
Finch!

40:36.999 --> 40:38.740
Finch! Finch!

40:38.871 --> 40:40.829
Please, no!
Finch, wake up!

40:40.960 --> 40:42.918
Stop! Finch!

40:43.049 --> 40:44.703
Finch!
Oh, my God. No!

40:44.833 --> 40:46.922
No!

40:47.053 --> 40:50.622
Hey. No, no, no, no, no.[Sobbing]

40:50.752 --> 40:54.539
No! [Sobbing]

40:54.669 --> 40:56.454
[Whirring]

41:01.763 --> 41:03.286
I'm gonna kill you.

41:03.417 --> 41:05.288
Why would you do that?

41:05.419 --> 41:08.074
I am the only one
who can save his life.

41:08.204 --> 41:10.903
Well, weare.

41:11.033 --> 41:12.905
♪

41:13.035 --> 41:14.167
Get them out of here.

41:14.297 --> 41:15.908
[Sobbing] Please!

41:16.038 --> 41:17.823
No! Please!

41:17.953 --> 41:20.782
Please. No, no, no,
no, no, no, no!
No!

41:20.913 --> 41:22.654
I'm gonna kill you.

41:22.784 --> 41:24.133
I'm gonna kill you!

41:24.264 --> 41:26.484
[Sherry crying]

41:26.614 --> 41:33.534
♪

41:33.665 --> 41:36.929
Better get to work,
Blue Jay.

41:37.059 --> 41:39.540
You've got a lot
to catch up on.

41:39.671 --> 41:43.588
We've got new patients
on their way this very moment.

41:43.718 --> 41:46.460
There's just one thing
we have to do first.

41:46.591 --> 41:47.896
What are you doing?

41:48.027 --> 41:49.550
♪

41:49.681 --> 41:51.073
What are you doing?

41:51.204 --> 41:52.074
What?

41:52.205 --> 41:54.555
♪

41:54.686 --> 41:57.123
We have to make sure
that Blue Jay

41:57.253 --> 41:59.299
can never hurt us...

41:59.429 --> 42:00.343
ever again.

42:00.474 --> 42:01.388
No.

42:01.519 --> 42:03.869
[Screaming]

42:03.999 --> 42:09.788
♪

42:25.586 --> 42:28.502
You know where
they're taking us?

42:28.633 --> 42:30.896
Your guess
is as good as mine.

42:33.638 --> 42:35.204
Why, Morgan?

42:35.335 --> 42:37.337
Why what?

42:37.467 --> 42:39.905
Why don't you think you can be
the person Mo needs you to be?

42:43.952 --> 42:45.780
You know,
what the hell happened?

42:45.911 --> 42:47.565
What's holding you back?

42:50.393 --> 42:53.701
We may not be alive long enough
for me to pass judgment on you.

43:00.665 --> 43:04.494
I been thinking
about a thing I did.

43:06.192 --> 43:11.414
Actually, a thing I didn'tdo
a long time ago.

43:11.545 --> 43:13.242
What?
It doesn't matter.

43:15.941 --> 43:19.205
Can you fix it?

43:19.335 --> 43:21.686
Not the worst of it, no.

43:21.816 --> 43:24.123
Some of it?
Maybe.

43:24.253 --> 43:25.472
[Chuckles]

43:25.603 --> 43:28.736
Then what the hell
are you doing here?

43:28.867 --> 43:31.130
She needs you.What are you saying?

43:31.260 --> 43:34.089
You need to do whatever it takes
so you can move forward.

43:34.220 --> 43:37.527
I'm not exactly in a situation
where I can call the shots here.

43:39.138 --> 43:41.488
[Coughs]

43:41.619 --> 43:43.098
I know.

43:43.229 --> 43:44.709
[Coughs]

43:44.839 --> 43:47.494
[Breathing heavily]

43:47.625 --> 43:50.018
You okay?

43:50.149 --> 43:52.064
[Wheezing]

43:52.194 --> 43:53.718
Hey! You --

43:53.848 --> 43:55.067
[Wheezing]

43:55.197 --> 43:57.678
You need to pull over!
Can you pull over?

43:57.809 --> 43:59.375
She can't breathe!

43:59.506 --> 44:00.942
[Coughing]

44:01.073 --> 44:08.776
♪

44:08.907 --> 44:11.387
Come on. Come on.
She needs oxygen.

44:11.518 --> 44:13.738
On your feet.
Come on.

44:13.868 --> 44:16.349
On your feet!

44:16.479 --> 44:17.437
Get her a tank.

44:17.567 --> 44:24.183
♪

44:24.313 --> 44:25.488
Morgan: Madison!

44:25.619 --> 44:28.187
♪

44:28.317 --> 44:31.712
Morgan, go!

44:31.843 --> 44:34.454
Go!

44:34.584 --> 44:36.064
Do what you need to do!

44:36.195 --> 44:39.154
♪

44:42.636 --> 44:44.464
Person:
After everything PADRE gave you,

44:44.594 --> 44:45.944
you betrayed him.

44:46.074 --> 44:48.076
♪

44:48.207 --> 44:50.862
This is how you're gonna
make it up to him.

44:50.992 --> 44:52.385
Woman:
PADRE's lied to all of us.

44:52.515 --> 44:55.388
We can find out
what else he's lied about.

44:55.518 --> 44:56.519
We'll let
the commander decide.

44:56.650 --> 44:57.695
Who's the commander?

44:57.825 --> 45:00.088
♪

45:00.219 --> 45:02.047
Madison: No more hiding
behind the mirror.

45:02.177 --> 45:05.224
♪

45:05.354 --> 45:06.529
Time to tell the truth.

45:06.660 --> 45:09.402
♪

45:12.361 --> 45:19.760
♪

45:19.891 --> 45:27.333
♪

45:27.463 --> 45:30.640
Chambliss: When we first meet
June in the second episode,

45:30.771 --> 45:33.643
she is in a very dark place,
and I would venture to say

45:33.774 --> 45:36.342
it's probably the darkest
we've ever seen her.

45:36.472 --> 45:37.996
[Growling]

45:38.126 --> 45:40.955
♪

45:41.086 --> 45:45.655
This is a June
who is on this mission,

45:45.786 --> 45:49.921
single-handedly hunting down
Collectors and taking them out.

45:50.051 --> 45:54.012
♪

45:54.142 --> 45:55.448
[Grunts]
[Grunts]

45:55.578 --> 45:56.884
But she's not just
taking them out.

45:57.015 --> 45:59.017
She's doing something
very specific.

45:59.147 --> 46:01.236
♪

46:01.367 --> 46:05.284
For her, it's a way of kind of
removing their power,

46:05.414 --> 46:07.634
saying, "You can't hold
a gun to my head

46:07.765 --> 46:10.463
'cause you literally
don't have trigger fingers."

46:10.593 --> 46:12.117
Man:
Cut our fingers off.

46:12.247 --> 46:13.727
Woman: You should have
been ready for them.

46:13.858 --> 46:16.730
They've been at this
for years now.

46:16.861 --> 46:19.080
I think reuniting
with Dwight and Sherry

46:19.211 --> 46:21.604
is a really complicated
moment for June.

46:21.735 --> 46:24.129
♪

46:24.259 --> 46:26.479
It's the last thing
that she wanted to happen.

46:26.609 --> 46:29.961
You don't have to answer our
questions, but he needs help.

46:30.091 --> 46:32.311
Alright,
we think he has appendicitis.

46:32.441 --> 46:33.486
He -- He needs surgery.

46:33.616 --> 46:35.488
June: That's your kid,
isn't it?

46:35.618 --> 46:37.707
The one you were pregnant with
when they found us on the rafts.

46:37.838 --> 46:40.319
And Dwight and Sherry
represent a real problem for her

46:40.449 --> 46:42.060
because these are people
from her past

46:42.190 --> 46:43.844
that she cares about
that need her help.

46:43.975 --> 46:45.715
How'd you get
on the boat?

46:45.846 --> 46:47.282
PADRE would never let you
spend time with your own kid.

46:47.413 --> 46:49.981
I got myself reassigned.So you lied.

46:50.111 --> 46:53.332
Once the surgery's done,
we'll take him back,

46:53.462 --> 46:55.725
and no one
will be the wiser.

46:55.856 --> 46:58.119
Which just shows you
how difficult it is

46:58.250 --> 47:00.643
to navigate at a place
like PADRE,

47:00.774 --> 47:04.996
where family is at the top
of the list of no-no's.

47:05.126 --> 47:06.519
I know where
we can do the surgery.

47:06.649 --> 47:09.087
Where?
I don't want
to answer any questions.

47:09.217 --> 47:10.697
I will take you there.
We will do this.

47:10.828 --> 47:12.568
But then you need to hold up
your end of the deal

47:12.699 --> 47:14.005
and get me that boat.We will.

47:14.135 --> 47:16.355
♪

47:16.485 --> 47:17.399
Come on, let's go.

47:17.530 --> 47:21.360
♪

47:21.490 --> 47:23.275
[Door creaks]

47:23.405 --> 47:25.538
[Walker growling]

47:25.668 --> 47:28.454
[Power whirs, machine beeps]

47:28.584 --> 47:31.109
♪

47:31.239 --> 47:34.503
What the hell
is this, huh?

47:34.634 --> 47:36.114
Who are these people?

47:36.244 --> 47:38.246
No questions.
That was the agreement.

47:38.377 --> 47:41.946
The whole kind of idea
for this train car

47:42.076 --> 47:43.991
that was kind of
this horror show

47:44.122 --> 47:47.777
of -- of these really twisted
medical experiments

47:47.908 --> 47:52.217
ultimately came out of us
thinking about June's story

47:52.347 --> 47:56.961
and what it could be that would
really set June off,

47:57.091 --> 47:59.180
the thing that PADRE
could have forced her to do

47:59.311 --> 48:01.530
that would -- would
kind of be beyond the pale.

48:01.661 --> 48:03.924
I used to work here.

48:04.055 --> 48:05.883
How come
we never heard about it?

48:06.013 --> 48:07.145
It was off the books.

48:07.275 --> 48:09.321
PADRE didn't want
anyone to know.

48:09.451 --> 48:12.150
Experiments
they were conducting.

48:12.280 --> 48:14.021
It was worse than dying
from the bites.

48:14.152 --> 48:16.589
Shrike tried to force me
to administer the treatments,

48:16.719 --> 48:18.678
but I wouldn't do it,
so I ran.

48:18.808 --> 48:20.593
The more we talked about it,
kind of the more excited we got

48:20.723 --> 48:24.510
and -- and just thinking of
all the really scary visuals

48:24.640 --> 48:26.251
we could create.

48:26.381 --> 48:28.209
It also allowed for the lighting
of the episode

48:28.340 --> 48:30.646
to be just really moody,

48:30.777 --> 48:34.607
and it just ended up
being kind of this gauntlet

48:34.737 --> 48:38.654
that June had to traverse
that put her kind of

48:38.785 --> 48:41.266
into direct confrontation
with her past

48:41.396 --> 48:43.529
and all these things
that PADRE had forced her to do.

48:43.659 --> 48:45.313
[Walker growling]

48:45.444 --> 48:48.186
♪

48:48.316 --> 48:50.188
How did you find me?

48:50.318 --> 48:52.625
I figured it was you
as soon as the Collectors

48:52.755 --> 48:56.063
started showing up to the island
without fingers.

48:56.194 --> 48:57.847
PADRE's got
something planned.

48:57.978 --> 48:59.414
You need to pick up
where you left off.

48:59.545 --> 49:01.895
I w-won't do that.

49:02.026 --> 49:04.985
You will. You just need
a little motivation.

49:05.116 --> 49:07.988
Chambliss: I think it's probably
one of the most brutal scenes

49:08.119 --> 49:10.469
that we've seen on -- on "Fear."

49:10.599 --> 49:13.341
And it really does paint Shrike

49:13.472 --> 49:18.303
in just a really,
really kind of vicious light.

49:18.433 --> 49:22.785
But it also raises a bunch
of questions about Shrike,

49:22.916 --> 49:25.005
about what happened in her past.

49:25.136 --> 49:27.007
Dwight: Finch, wake up!

49:27.138 --> 49:28.139
Finch, wake up!

49:28.269 --> 49:30.837
Finch! Finch!
Finch! No! No!

49:30.968 --> 49:32.578
[Sobbing] No!

49:32.708 --> 49:34.797
Please!

49:34.928 --> 49:36.060
I'm gonna kill you.

49:36.190 --> 49:38.062
Why would you do that?

49:38.192 --> 49:41.456
I am the only one
who can save his life.

49:41.587 --> 49:44.198
Well, weare.

49:46.113 --> 49:49.682
♪

49:49.812 --> 49:53.903
Goldberg: Well, when Madison met
Morgan at the end of Season 7,

49:54.034 --> 49:55.601
Morgan only had one goal,

49:55.731 --> 49:57.690
which was he wanted
his daughter back.

49:57.820 --> 49:59.126
At the end of this episode,

49:59.257 --> 50:01.476
she's really scratching
at this with Morgan

50:01.607 --> 50:05.872
and wondering why -- why he
doesn't feel he can protect Mo.

50:06.003 --> 50:08.483
Madison:
What's holding you back?

50:08.614 --> 50:10.485
She needs you.What are you saying?

50:10.616 --> 50:13.271
You need to do whatever it takes
so you can move forward.

50:13.401 --> 50:14.968
She knows how important it is

50:15.099 --> 50:16.622
for Morgan
to be able to fight for Mo.

50:16.752 --> 50:19.277
And she's doing everything she
can to make that happen for him.

50:19.407 --> 50:21.453
[Grunting]

50:21.583 --> 50:23.585
♪

50:23.716 --> 50:25.065
Morgan, go!

50:25.196 --> 50:27.198
♪

50:27.328 --> 50:28.851
Do what you need to do!

